	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hmm, ok. Now, lets say I wanted to make a game with characters from different games... and putting them in, well, different games (example: using the first level in mario bros.... but with samus). That's the best way I can describe my vision, but if it's too vague I can emphasize more later. Anyway, is that at all possible, or would that require something other than 6502asm?
<br />
<br />(Ok, I might have found a site (<a href="http://www.programmersheaven.com/zone5/cat440/15550.htm" class="postlink">http://www.programmersheaven.com/zone5/cat440/15550.htm</a>) to download the "6502asm"... but I don't know where to begin... first the "help" file doesn't explain how to begin creating the rom. Is there some sort of link to the actual language to use? 
<br />
<br />Also on the nesdev site, there are some roms that include a "source code"... is that compatable with 6502asm?

		

